<?xml version="1.0"?><h:html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2002/xforms" xmlns:ev="http://www.w3.org/2001/xml-events" xmlns:h="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:jr="http://openrosa.org/javarosa" xmlns:odk="http://www.opendatakit.org/xforms" xmlns:orx="http://openrosa.org/xforms" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"><h:head><h:title>OSCE B.sc 2nd Year Medical Sug._Removing medication from an ampule</h:title><model odk:xforms-version="1.0.0"><instance><data id="osce1_form" version="1.1"><intro><reserved_name_for_field_list_labels_3/><step1/><step2/><step3/><step4/><step5/><step6/><step7/><step8/><step9/><step10/><step11/><step12/><step13/><step14/><step15/><step16/><step17/><step18/><step19/><step20/></intro><meta><instanceID/></meta></data></instance><bind nodeset="/data/intro/reserved_name_for_field_list_labels_3" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step1" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step2" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step3" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step4" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step5" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step6" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step7" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step8" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step9" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step10" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step11" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step12" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step13" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step14" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step15" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step16" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step17" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step18" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step19" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step20" required="true()" type="string"/><bind jr:preload="uid" nodeset="/data/meta/instanceID" readonly="true()" type="string"/></model></h:head><h:body class="pages"><group appearance="field-list" ref="/data/intro"><select1 appearance="label" ref="/data/intro/reserved_name_for_field_list_labels_3"><label> </label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step1"><label>Goal: The medication will be removed in a sterile manner, be free from glass shards, and be prepared in the proper dose.
Gather equipment. Check the medication order against the original physician's order according to agency policy. Clarify any inconsistencies. Check the patient's chart for allergies.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step2"><label>Know the actions, special nursing considerations, safe dose ranges, purpose of administration, and adverse effects of the medications to be administered. Consider the appropriateness of the medication for this patient.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step3"><label>Perform hand hygiene.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step4"><label>Move the medication cart to the outside of the patient's room or prepare for administration in the medication area.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step5"><label>Unlock the medication cart or drawer.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step6"><label>Prepare medications for one patient at a time.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step7"><label>Read the Medication order and select the proper medication from the patient's medication drawer or unit stock.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step8"><label>Compare the label with the medication order. Check expiration dates and perform calculations, If necessary. Scan the barcode on the package, if required</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step9"><label>Tap the stem of the ampule or twist your wrist quickly while holding the ampule vertically.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step10"><label>Wrap a small gauze pad around the neck of the ampule.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step11"><label>Use a snapping motion to break off the top of the ampule along the scored line at its neck. Always break away from your body.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step12"><label>Attach filter needle to syringe. Remove the cap from the filter needle by pulling it straight off. Insert the filter needle into the ampule, being careful not to touch the rim.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step13"><label>Withdraw medication in the amount ordered plus a small amount more (approximately 30%). Do not inject air into the solution. Use either of the following methods:
a. Insert the tip of the needle into the ampule, which is upright on a flat surface, and withdraw fluid into the syringe. Touch plunger at knob only.
b. Insert the tip of the needle into the ampule and invert the ampule. Keep the needle centered and not touching the sides of the ampule. Withdraw fluid into syringe. Touch plunger at knob only.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step14"><label>Wait until the needle has been withdrawn to tap the syringe and expel the air carefully by pushing on the plunger. Check the amount of medication in the syringe with the medication dose and discard any surplus according to facility policy.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step15"><label>Recheck the label with the medication order.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step16"><label>Engage safety guard on filter needle and remove. Discard the filter needle in a suitable container. Attach appropriate administration device to syringe.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step17"><label>Discard the ampule in a suitable container.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step18"><label>Lock the medication cart before leaving it.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step19"><label>Perform hand hygiene.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step20"><label>Proceed with administration, based on prescribed route</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1></group></h:body></h:html>